Here's a collection of four Australian anti-drug ads. The last two are fairly old, because I remember seeing them on the TV.
The only real problem Australia suffers from drugs is thier price, they are roughly three times more expensive in real terms than say, in europe.
This means that drug use is a financially crippling excercise for a large percentage of Australians. This not only means that they are likely to borrow or steal money from thier friends, there is a high popability of descending into a system of starvation economy, where you live hand to mouth, working by the hour to get money for more drugs.

This was originally written as a reply to an entry by However, it kept growing until it was to long to fit in a comment.. The original comment is here Have you ever read 'The Prince' by Machiavelli? Much of the current actions of americas leaders can be explained in that light, ie, whatever the country was founded upon, it has now become a very different creature. It's not really that unusual if you look to history, many countries have more or less ruled the world at one time or another, the Spanish, the Dutch, the Pourtegese, the English.. and they did it in a way that has hardly changed since the time of Rome, by invading other counties either overtly by making them colonies, or covertly, making them client states. America is rich and powerful for the same reason as the Romans, they have what is called currency by fiat, which means that thier currency is not backed by anything tangible, such as the gold standard, it is backed, essentially, by military power. The american dollar is worth something sinply because the americans say that it is. Many client states have the value of thier currency linked to the US dollar, thus propigating the 'magic' of intangible worth. IMHO, the bloodless coup that put GW Bush in power was the turning point. Although it had been leading up to something like this for ages. Democracy has become a meaningless ritual by which the people reassure themselves of thier own powerlessness. it is obvious that the elections are rigged. By definition, there are many many more poor people than rich ones, so if democracy was truley representative, it would not always be the priviliged and wealthy who are elected. The fact that elections can be influenced by money means that it will be the wealthiest who are elected. So who are the wealthiest people? The products that generate the most global income are Drugs (for which you need prohibition, otherwise, you would not be able to buy a gram of heroin in afghanistan and sell it for $500 in Sydney.) and Weapons (for which you need war, otherwise, no one will buy them.) The first historical example of this process can be seen in the Opium Wars that the British fought with China. By taking control of the opium growing region of Pakistan, the British essentially cornered the world opium market. Once they obtained a monopoly, they raised the price, which put pressure on the Chinese. As the price rose, people had to do more desperate things to obtain the money to buy opium. The British would send ships to china loaded with opium and they would return packed with silver, which is how the british managed to accumulate enough silver reserves to make the pound sterling (wich was of course, equal to a pound of silver) a dominant currency. Eventually, the Chinese emperor outlawed the use of opium and banned british ships from chinese ports, which is what started the first opium war. Of course, prohibition merely raised the price even further, resulting in greater social turmoil for the chinese and greater domination of the pound. (argh, this message is too fucking long.. continued in next comment ) Going to war to secure drug supply is a win-win situation. The price of the drug rises, making money and the cost of the war also makes money. By instituting a global ban on drugs through the league of nations, the americans ensured that no country would be able to supply free heroin to everyone who needed it, therefore ensuring a large flow of money to the americans from every country in the world. A quick examination of the American power structure makes it obvious that they are the drug dealers. Practically every person in a position of real power in America went to school at Yale and belongs to the Skull and Bones. Skull and Bones was founded by Opium smugglers. The immense profits made them powerful enough to fuck with entire countries. check out http://www.answers.com/topic/skull-and-bones-historical-connections (this article was originally on wikipedia, but has been removed for some reason.. it is very informative... =) Those who are born into power, wealth and privilege do not care about the poor, they do not even have an understanding of the concept. Like kings through time immemorial, they are only concerned about the people if something happens that threatens thier economic base. In truth, aristocracy never went away, it has just retreated so far from the common man that most people could not even _begin_ to understand the purpose behind thier actions. Thus, when you talk about america and are confused, because it's actions are different to it's people, you have to realise that the america you hate is basically the Narco-Military complex and thier goals are simply to make as much money as possible selling drugs and weapons, regardless of the consequences. After all, why should they care? They have all the drugs they want and live in places untouched by poverty or war, far from the sufferring of the people who thier actions affect.. (whew.. what a rant...) =)

There's some rather disturbing shit happening in Angola in Africa at the moment, an outbreak of Marburg virus (a viral haemorrhagic fever, or VHF) has killed 132 people, including 4-5 foreign doctors. 9 people are currently in isolation in Italy, after a doctor returned from Angola and fell ill. What is particuarly worrying about this outbreak is that out of 140 cases, there have been 132 fatalities, which means that at the moment, this virus has a mortality rate of approx 95% After doing a bit of research, I came across some interesting contradictions: Marburg supposedly has an incubation period of 3-9 days. Infact, the relatiely short incubation period of most filioviruses has been a major reason that they have not spread beyond rural areas. According to the WHO Marburg virus disease is an acute febrile illness accompanied by severe haemorrhagic manifestations. The disease has an incubation period of 3 to 9 days. In the earliest stage of infection, symptoms are non-specific and may be easily confused with more common diseases, including malaria, yellow fever, and typhoid fever. A severe watery diarrhoea, abdominal pain, nausea and vomiting are early symptoms, as are severe chest and lung pains, sore throat, and cough. A high proportion of cases develop severe haemorrhagic manifestations between days 5 and 7, most frequently affecting the gastrointestinal tract and the lungs. A characteristic rash usually appears at this time, sometimes involving the whole body. However, according to Reuters: "The incubation period is 21 days so we must reinforce the surveillance in neighbouring provinces and especially in Luanda," Vice Minister for Health Jose Van Dunem told Reuters. The incredible spread of this virus to foriegn health workers is also a worry. Most western trained medics are familiar with the concept of barrier nursing and would utilise such techniques when dealing with a patient that was even suspected of having a VHF. Source here This leads me to a very, very spooky possibility, which is that the virus is transmissible through the air (droplet transmission). Actually, there is already some evidence to support this. According to promed, this strain of marburg can be transmitted by sweat and saliva, unlike Ebola, for example, which is mainly transmitted by blood. Although contraversial, there are some who believe that there is a historical precedent for a VHF which is air-transmissible and has a 21 day incubation period. The Plague of Athens wiped out the ancient Greeks. It was carried to Greece by a warship that came back from Africa. According to historical sources, this disease was an airborne hemmoragic fever with an incubation period of 21 days. The first week, you were asymptomatic and non-infectious. Second week, you were asymtomatic and infectious, third week, you developed symptoms. It is said that the long incubation period of this disease is what made it so terrible, since there was no way of knowing who was sick and in closed enviroments like ships, the virus spread rapidly. The benchmark history text of the Plague of Athens was written by Thucydides. You can read it here This article from the CDC puts forward the argument that from the historical description, a VHF was the most likely culprit. The Thucydides Syndrome: Ebola Reemergent? I'm going to do a bit more research on this, this post is mainly just a place to get all the bits of info down. If anyone has any more info on this, i would appreciate it.
